issue_comments.body:
Hi, this repository is just a mirror; it's not monitored for pull requests (hence it was years before this was noticed) and nobody has the ability to merge your pull request, sorry. It's much appreciated if you want to contribute fixes to GNOME, but you'll need to do so on GNOME Bugzilla.

Anyway, the change is not right -- the account manager is already freed in dispose (using `g_clear_object`) so it's guaranteed to already be NULL in finalize.

Hi, thanks for these changes. They look good (except it should be split into three commits instead of just one), but they have already been integrated upstream in the past year and a half.

This repository is just a mirror; it's not monitored for pull requests (hence why this was never noticed) and nobody has the ability to merge or even close your pull request, sorry. It's much appreciated if you want to contribute fixes to GNOME, but you'll need to do so on GNOME Bugzilla.

Thank you for contributing to empathy!

empathy uses Bugzilla for code review.

https://wiki.gnome.org/Newcomers/CodeContributionWorkflow
and follow the instructions there to upload your change to Bugzilla.
